Authorship proof (cryptographic commitment)
--------------------------------------------
The original author holds a secret passphrase. Its SHA-256 commitment is
published here and in lib/common.ps1 ($AicAuthorCommitment):

    sha256 = 4c4b757e130d8155a32609c191edd769164976edaff1e4798b6d15ad3f872612

The passphrase itself is NOT contained anywhere in this repository. Only the
original author can produce a string whose SHA-256 equals the commitment above.
Anyone can verify a claimed phrase with:

    allincodex verify-author "<phrase>"

A correct phrase prints "AUTHOR VERIFIED". This lets the original author prove
authorship at any time, even against a fork that strips the visible marks, while
never revealing the secret.

